### User Profile Update API Tests
### Base URL configuration
@base_url = http://localhost:8000

### Test 1: Get current user profile (requires authentication)
GET {{base_url}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### Test 2: Update user profile information
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/update
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "mobile_number": "+1234567890"
}

### Test 3: Update user profile with partial data
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/update
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Jane"
}

### Test 4: Update user password
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "current_password": "old_password_123",
  "new_password": "NewPassword123",
  "confirm_password": "NewPassword123"
}

### Test 5: Test password validation - passwords don't match
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "current_password": "old_password_123",
  "new_password": "NewPassword123",
  "confirm_password": "DifferentPassword123"
}

### Test 6: Test password validation - weak password
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "current_password": "old_password_123",
  "new_password": "weak",
  "confirm_password": "weak"
}

### Test 7: Test email validation - invalid email format
PUT {{base_url}}/user/profile/update
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email-format"
}

### Test 8: Test mobile number validation - invalid format
